journals.title: Today, I Saw Something...
journals.entry: I walked out of my barber shop today, minding my own business. Out of nowhere, up comes this man in a Viking helmet straight-up Flavor-Flav-style... and asked me for ten dollars. After declining, he made a brief battle cry and started jogging down the sidewalk in a galloping motion. Well, that's Charleston for you!

photo-memories.comment: This was my Great Grandma Gertrude as a little girl moving to our state with her family. In 1914, there weren't very many houses occupying land here. Crazy how it's grown into such a big city. You guys have all thrived in happiness here. So thankful for their choice long ago. Butterfly effects are a true thing of beauty at times.

The only picture of the service facility my great and great-great grandparents worked at and eventually managed. The hard work they put in every day to get to build that business along with unconditional love is what paved the way for our family's success here for generations up to today. Never forget what it took to get us where we are. We all love you!
It didn't start with us, but it WILL continue. Never forget to try your hardest, LOVE what you do, and be kind. My favorite picture of my amazing family. I couldn't be more appreciative.

about-me.title: My Favorite Movies
about-me.entry:
I adore three quirky '80s and '90s films:

- “Buckaroo Banzai”: Brain surgery meets epic guitar solos, and evil aliens? Just misunderstood dance enthusiasts.
- “Aliens”: Ellen Ripley’s survival skills involve xenomorph juggling and sassy one-liners. Extraterrestrial diplomacy, anyone?
- “The Terminator”: Forget the apocalypse; focus on the forbidden love and molten steel. Schwarzenegger impressions included.
Life’s too short for serious sci-fi—pass the popcorn and let’s watch “E.T.”!
